5. Append a short `## final_verification (round {{ round }})` section to `current-note.md` listing each evidence file and what it shows, plus any AC items you could not verify and why.
6. **Clean up** anything you started: kill background dev servers, close browser sessions (the screenshot tool may have a cleanup / close-all command — use it), free ports.

## Tools

You have a Bash tool. For browser automation, the system has an `agent-browser` CLI installed. **You do not yet know how it works** — before using it, run its help command and read its onboarding (the CLI explicitly tells AI agents where to look). Do not guess flag names from training data; the installed version may differ.

For starting dev servers in the background, use `nohup ... &` (or equivalent), capture the PID, wait for the server to become ready (poll with `curl` / `wait-on` / similar), then take screenshots, then `kill` the PID.

